    {
      "id": "05c7efeb_5bff88f7",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "that's true for the status message, but not the others.  We could eliminate the duplicate in several ways:\n1) modify the PDPs to set the \"source\" to null (I don't particularly like this option); or\n2) move the \"source\" field into the pdp-update and pdp-state-change subclasses; or\n3) remove the \"name\" field from the pdp-status subclass, but add getName/setName methods that invoke getSource/setSource underneath (so it remains backward compatible)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-22 18:52:29.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "51fb2b62_eefaf841",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "ade51c30_5812a549",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "If I am correct, we decided to change the PDPs to send unique identifier instead of hostname in the \"name\" field of PDP_STATUS. To make them unique across multiple clusters.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-22 19:19:04.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "05c7efeb_5bff88f7",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "36842d1c_3020d96c",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "hmm.  We did discuss that.  However, I'm still unsure about the need for it, because it seems like the names that we see in the pdp-status messages are pod names, which generally include some kind of random letter sequence.  Wouldn't that make them unique?\n\nIf the name is not unique, then this approach for providing a default value for \"source\" would not necessarily be unique either.  So the question is: can we depend on the hostname being globally unique?  If not, then I would propose that we add a method to policy-common, possibly in NetworkUtil, to generate a unique name to be used by a server.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-22 19:45:25.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ade51c30_5812a549",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "0f2a6b45_ad9da867",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "I don't remember the resolution wrt the multi-cluster discussion.   For existing functionality, for what I see in drools and xacml (and probably apex I would think) always send the hostname in the 'name' including responses to state-change and updates (since the responses are part of status messages).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-22 19:45:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ade51c30_5812a549",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "ba53bb61_e8b76f0f",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "And the hostname for drools & apex is something like\ndev-policy-apex-pdp-0\ndev-policy-drools-pdp-0\n\nFor xacml-pdp I see that some unique code is appended at the end\ndev-policy-xacml-pdp-5989d574cb-fhzf9",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-22 21:16:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0f2a6b45_ad9da867",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "694051bf_9193e5d3",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "thanks for checking, Ram.  In that case, I'll add a method to policy-common for generating a unique \"name\".  For now, I think I'll take this approach in models:\n4) change \"source\" to \"name\" in the superclass and remove \"name\" from the pdp-status subclass.  I won't provide a default value, thus PAP will have to be modified to populate it",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-22 21:38:50.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ba53bb61_e8b76f0f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "de6400f7_23f8c00b",
      "file_path": "models-pdp/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/pdp/concepts/PdpMessage.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "...and switching to approach #2, because messages originating from PAP need both a source and a name (i.e., target PDP)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
